    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat, then pat your <strong>chicken thighs</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken thighs</strong>, skin-side down and cook for an initial 10 min or until the skins have browned and crisped</p><p>Once browned, reduce heat to medium-high then turn the chicken thighs and cook them for a further 8 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
